         <abstract>
            <p>We prove that the problem of multiple integration in the Korobov class E&lt;sub&gt;α, d&lt;/sub&gt; is intractable since the number of function evaluations required to achieve a worst case error less than 1 is exponential in the dimension.</p>
          </abstract>
